claim.claim-text:
1. A method for optically scanning and measuring an object by a laser scanner, comprising the steps of:
modulating an emission light beam with a target frequency;
emitting the emission light beam;
receiving a reception light beam reflected or otherwise scattered from the object in surroundings of the laser scanner, with a measuring clock, as a multiplicity of samples by a light receiver;
determining in each case at least a distance from the laser scanner to the object from phase angles of the multiplicity of samples for a plurality of measuring points by a control and evaluation device; and
correcting a phase shift caused by a distance difference of temporal adjacent samples to correct the determined distances.
